    • Field Detail

      • PRIORITY_ACCURACY

        public static final int PRIORITY_ACCURACY
        Indicates the priority over location accuracy.

        This priority relies on the satellite system to locate the current location of the user device. It can provide a better location result in open areas.

        To use this priority, your application needs to apply for the ohos.permission.LOCATION permission and obtain user authorization.

        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_FAST_FIRST_FIX

        public static final int PRIORITY_FAST_FIRST_FIX
        Indicates the priority over fast location.

        If this priority is selected, the system reports the real-time location result immediately upon receiving the location request.

        To use this priority, your application needs to apply for the ohos.permission.LOCATION permission and obtain user authorization.

        Since:
        1
        See Also:

      • PRIORITY_LOW_POWER

        public static final int PRIORITY_LOW_POWER
        Indicates the priority over power efficiency.

        This priority relies on the Wi-Fi hotspots or cell IDs to estimate the current location of the user device. It consumes less power than the location accuracy priority but requires that the user device is able to access the Internet.

        To use this priority, your application needs to apply for the ohos.permission.LOCATION permission and obtain user authorization.

        Since:
        1

      • SCENE_NO_POWER

        public static final int SCENE_NO_POWER
        Indicates the scenario in which your application does not proactively start the location service for a higher battery efficiency.

        When responding to another application requesting the same location service, the system marks a copy of location result to your application. In this way, your application will not consume extra power for obtaining the user location.

        In this scenario, the system reports the location result at a minimum interval of 1s by default.

        To use this scenario, your application needs to apply for the ohos.permission.LOCATION permission and obtain user authorization.

        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Constructor Detail

      • RequestParam

        public RequestParam​(int scenario)
             throws IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a RequestParam object for the location request based on the location scenario type. You are advised to use the location scenario types defined by the system. Unless otherwise required, you do not need to set other parameters for this data class. For details about the location scenario types, go to the respective link:
        • Automotive navigation: SCENE_NAVIGATION
        • Trajectory tracking: SCENE_TRAJECTORY_TRACKING
        • Ride hailing: SCENE_CAR_HAILING
        • Life service: SCENE_DAILY_LIFE_SERVICE
        • Low-power consumption: SCENE_NO_POWER

        The location priority policy configured by will become invalid after the RequestParam object is initialized using this method.

        However, you can still choose to configure parameters specific to reporting of location results, such as the time interval, distance between locations, and location accuracy threshold. For details, see setTimeInterval(int), setDistanceInterval(int), and setMaxAccuracy(float).

        Parameters:
        scenario - Specifies the location scenario type.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the specified location scenario type has not been defined in RequestParam.
        Since:
        1

      • RequestParam

        public RequestParam​(int priority,
                    int timeInterval,
                    int distanceInterval)
             throws IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a RequestParam object for the location request based on parameters such as the location priority policy.

        You need to set the location priority policy, and the time interval and moving distance for reporting the location result.

        For details about the location priority policy, go to the respective link:

        • Location accuracy: PRIORITY_ACCURACY
        • Low-power consumption: PRIORITY_LOW_POWER
        • Fast location: PRIORITY_FAST_FIRST_FIX

        If you need to set the location accuracy threshold, refer to setMaxAccuracy(float). The default value is 0.0,which indicates that the location accuracy is not applied when reporting the location result.

        Parameters:
        priority - Specifies the location priority policy.
        timeInterval - Specifies the minimum time interval (in seconds) for reporting the location result. A valid value is greater than or equal to 1. The default value 0 will be used if the specified value is smaller than 1.
        distanceInterval - Specifies the minimum moving distance (in meters) for reporting the location result. A valid value is greater than or equal to 1. The default value 0 will be used if the specified value is smaller than 1.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the specified location priority policy has not been defined in RequestParam.
        Since:
        1

      • setTimeInterval

        public void setTimeInterval​(int value)
        Sets the minimum time interval (in seconds) for reporting the location result.

        The system ensures that the time interval between two consecutive location results is greater than or equal to the specified value.

        The default value is 0, which indicates that the system reports the location result to the application immediately after successful location.

        Parameters:
        value - Specifies the minimum time interval (in meters) for reporting the location result. A valid value is greater than or equal to 1. The default value 0 will be used if the specified value is smaller than 1.
        Since:
        1

      • getDistanceInterval

        public int getDistanceInterval​()
        Obtains the minimum moving distance in the RequestParam object.

        If the moving distance between the current location and the previously reported location exceeds the specified value, the location result is reported to the application.

        Returns:
        Returns the minimum moving distance for reporting the location result. The default value is 0, which indicates that the minimum moving distance is not applied when reporting the location result.
        Since:
        1
